You sir are a coward. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umistressshino.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mistress Shino</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.iconbazaar.com/dots/animated/pg09/9anidot6c.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/16/01 5:16:01 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://communities.msn.ca/_Secure/0MACAl0sRsZ1DrERVfJZ4CaEL7myP5FXdMBtnmimt6FkTtYjawey*Q0yYyx5niflYE6b4LffNSzQGZOML!1mcPQ/p.jpg WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=188></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The sad situation we find ourselves in...</span><hr size=1> You make it sound like being exiled to Canada is a bad thing, I personally wouldnt want to live in any other country in the world. Sure, we could never win our own war (the new york state transit police outnumbers the Canadian military, and I bet they are better equiped aswell) but we dont need to. And now I'm gonna stop writing cause I realise this post is totally off topic, yet im still gonna hit add reply. <p><center><i>"Breathe the pressure,
