</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugladetree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gladetree</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/16/01 5:32:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> um</span><hr size=1>   This situation is not about cowardice or bravery.  This is about who in the hell are we going to kill and why.  I don't think we're going to kill the right people, and I think it's going to get a lot of us killed.  If I knew where the terrorists were then I'd be more than happy to fight my way to their front door and blow them the fuck up, but we don't know where they are and if we did then we wouldn't be sitting in this limbo.  <br>
<br>
  The fact of the matter is that we cannot fight this kind of battle with conventional military intervention. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukytherion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kytherion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 238<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/16/01 5:49:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yep, I'm sick.</span><hr size=1> &quot;This situation is not about cowardice or bravery.&quot;<br>
<br>
The fuck it isn't. No one's even said the word &quot;draft&quot; yet, and you're making reservations in fucking Canada.<br>
<br>
Where the hell do you think the Canadians will be? Probably the same place as the British...fighting right along side us. How you could even conceive of holding your head up in a country fighting YOUR war  is beyond me.<br>
<br>
What will you say when the first Canadian widow asks you where you're from? Will you even have the courage to apologize for your shame?<br>
<br>
If you were brave, you'd refuse to fight and serve your time in jail. It's the law, it's been that way since the day you were born. Now you want to opt out because one of your fucking video games might turn real.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;The fact of the matter is that we cannot fight this kind of battle with conventional military intervention.&quot;<br>
<br>
Oh yes, we can. The question is whether or not certain spineless whelps, such as yourself, will be able to stomach the sight of a real war. I'm guessing no, so calm your delicate nerves, my precious little tulip.<br>
<br>
Christ, I don't know why I'm bothering. Not like they conscript women anyway. You'll be just fine. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugladetree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gladetree</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/16/01 6:32:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> think...</span><hr size=1> This isn't MY war you fascist ass.  This is the &quot;war&quot; that we so happily ignored for decades when it occured in other countries but now comes to the forefront as we finally become victim to it.<br>
<br>
This struggle is not new, and the issues have not sprung up overnight.  Our seeming willingness to lash out with absolutely no sense of what the hell we're doing is what's new.  This fight is NOT conventional.  We will NOT fight a &quot;winnable&quot; war in Afghanistan.  Hell, this whole concept of &quot;war&quot; is a fucking joke and nothing but a rallying cry for Bush to do whatever he wants.<br>
<br>
Fine, let him thump his chest and send people wherever the hell he wants.  It'll sure make people feel better.  What happens after we've landed in some god-forsaken part of the globe and the troops collectively go &quot;wtf?&quot; is what i'm opposed to...<br>
<br>
If you really think this war CAN be fought conventionally then please, by all means, have fun.  It's a great symbol. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaolen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aolen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/16/01 6:57:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: think...</span><hr size=1> Well Gladetree,<br>
As a former member of the armed services, I can say I would go if they sent me. As far as I'm conserned any gov't that harbours this scum is just as guilty as the terrorists themselves.  I'm sure people said the same thing you have about Nazi Germany during WWII. To me this is a just cause. As far as draft goes, I doubt it goes that far. And if it does, you can always file as a conscientious objector. Worst case, ya go to prison. But if ya run, ya are a coward and your opinion don't mean jack.<br>
<br>
Aolen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukytherion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kytherion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/16/01 7:03:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Oops, you dropped your integrity.</span><hr size=1> I'm a &quot;fascist&quot; because I know my duty?<br>
<br>
Listen carefully. This is America. No one cares what you do. Waste your life, fuck around, be successful or don't. How you spend your life is your business, a freedom that many men and a few women have died for.<br>
<br>
Except for one thing. When they call you to fight, you go. <br>
<br>
You don't theorize, you don't rationalize, you don't proclaim your opinion and think that gives you an out. You don't point cleverly at what the TV has told you regarding the strategy of the war that hasn't even happened yet, and think you should get to stay.<br>
<br>
I don't like Bush myself, you smarmy little rodent, but that doesn't change the nature of my citizenship, or the responsibility that goes with it. <br>
<br>
Go and fight, or stay and go to prison. Or leave and never come back. One rule, and you've known it since the day you had to register. When you signed up, it didn't mean you would get drafted if you felt like it. It meant you'd get drafted when your country needed you.<br>
<br>
I know pacifists that will stay and protest, and serve their time, if it comes to that. You, on the other hand, will run like the rat you are. But for the love of all that is holy, don't inflict yourself on the Canadians. The cowardly filth you've posted here is humiliating enough.<br>
<br>
Greenland is lovely this time of year. Stay awhile. It's amazing that your father was able to sustain an erection long enough to spawn you.<br>
<br>
I'm done with your worthless ass. We'd all be better of without you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ushadolok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadolok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/16/01 7:09:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: think...</span><hr size=1> Its sad that it took such a horrible event to create this devotion to ridding the world of terrorism.  Yes, it has gone on for a LONG time, too long, but never on this scale.  <br>
<br>
Gladetree, you think you are living FREELY in the United States and no one suffered so that you may do so?  Go watch Saving Private Ryan and get a *glimpse* of what Americans have gone through to ensure your rights to be posting shallow remarks such as yours.  You live FREELY because others have given their LIVES for it.  <br>
<br>
We all take for granted our military, police, fireman and other organizations that sacrifice daily to help the lives of others.  <br>
<br>
Glade, I'd imagine it would be too much to ask of you to help an elderly woman cross the street.  Get out of the United States, I dont want your values trickling down the gene pool so that there are more ungrateful bastards like you around.  <br>
<br>
Shadolok <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umuzaak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Muzaak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/16/01 7:13:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The sad situation we find ourselves in...</span><hr size=1> Gladtree what the fuck are we supposed to do? Just roll over? Bring Bin Laden to the US and execute him? What good would that do? <br>
<br>
The problem is with cowards who think they can run to Canada or even anonymously bomb the World Trade Center! Yes, both are in the same camp because each cannot face their enemies or difficuties in a constructive manner. Enough of psychology.<br>
<br>
Pull your head out of your ass! The situation we are in is not just the doing of the USA. It is a combination of actions and now it is time to go forward. I will gladly volunteer to drive a tank for my country and grease the treads of the tank with the corpses of terrorists!<br>
<br>
Muzaak -- Bard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utriff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Triff</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.maclem.com/images/triff/triffdot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 310<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/16/01 7:23:10 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.maclem.com/images/triff/trifflogo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The sad situation we find ourselves in...</span><hr size=1> Well shit, I'll argue the other side of the spectrum (the draft) if Glade won't. Where the hell did you people get these ideas?<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> This country was made strong by the patriotism and selfless service to their country.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This is bullshit. This country was made strong by capitalism and all its implications (read: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> freedom</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->). America was founded because all the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> other</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> countries were based on that sort of &quot;sacrifice yourself to everyone else&quot; shit. This country wasn't founded on communism. Americans are not born to serve. People were meant to have rights, and the definition of a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> right</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> does <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> end with a footnote saying, &quot;until and unless the majority says otherwise.&quot; When a man enlists to fight a war, he fights because the country he's fighting for is great and he will die rather than accept anything less.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> No one's even said the word &quot;draft&quot; yet, and you're making reservations in fucking Canada.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Just because no one's said it doesn't mean it's not a real possibility. Leaving something unnamed doesn't negate its existence.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> How you could even conceive of holding your head up in a country fighting YOUR war is beyond me.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
What Glade said: this is not <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> my</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> war. I'm sorry about what happened in New York. I think the people who orchestrated it should be killed. But I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> don't</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> want to risk <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> my</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> life to head out and fight some ambiguous enemy in order to help the large mass referred to as the &quot;American public&quot; feel like everything is being resolved.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> What will you say when the first Canadian widow asks you where you're from? Will you even have the courage to apologize for your shame?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I'll tell her I came to Canada because the US government was trying to revoke my right to live.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If you were brave, you'd refuse to fight and serve your time in jail. It's the law, it's been that way since the day you were born.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Sorry, I don't buy into that whole &quot;If it's been around this long, it <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> can't</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be wrong!&quot; thing. I also don't believe that the judgement of the people running our government is infallible.<br>
<br>
I think it's sick for a &quot;free country&quot; to be so full of people who would want to force others to fight for them. I'm happy for the people who gladly sign up. They do it of their own will. But I'll be damned if I'll accept this government forcing people to fight for them (again, even!); all it does is turn people into slaves. Do you think the drafted soldiers are going to feel any kind of fiery will to fight for a country that just shoved them out onto a battlefield to be cannon fodder?<br>
<br>
